generated_reports.report: Findings: Trachea and both main bronchi are open. Main mediastinal vascular structures, heart contour, and size are normal. Thoracic aorta diameter is normal. No pericardial effusion-thickening was observed. Thoracic esophagus is calibrated and no significant tumoral wall thickening was detected. No pathologically enlarged lymph nodes were found in the prevascular, pre-paratracheal, subcarinal, or bilateral hilar-axillary regions. When examined in the lung parenchyma window; a few millimetric nonspecific nodules are seen in both lungs. No pleural effusion-thickening was detected. The upper abdominal organs included in the sections are normal. No space-occupying lesions were found in the liver included in the sections. Bilateral adrenal gland regions are normal and no space-occupying lesions were found. The bony structures included in the examination area are normal. Vertebral corpus heights are preserved. Impression: A few millimetric nonspecific nodules in both lungs.
